  "doc_id": "26006",
  "text": "In contrast to RBCs GUVs did not exhibit any observable shape transformations prior to rupture. The reason for that lied in the absence of any internal structure of the GUVs. As already mentioned above the bilayer-coupling model requires the existence of an elastic membrane skeleton coupled to the membrane to reproduce all observed RBC shapes [CITATION_1] . Additionally, GUVs produced by electroformation have initially a high membrane tension [CITATION_2] , evident in the perfectly spherical shape, and no access area available for shape transformations. These characteristics made GUVs suitable models for spherocytes.",
